text: Atilije Venturini (12 August 1908 - 15 June 1944) was a Yugoslav swimmer. He competed in two events at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1908 births Category:1944 deaths Category:Yugoslav male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Yugoslavia Category:Swimmers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing
